The paper deals with planning for robotic manipulation tasks in cluttered environments, which is a common problem in robotics. The use of collision avoidance schemes and real-time obstacle removal suggests a focus on robotics and control (cs.RO). The use of algorithms and computational methods for planning and optimization suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of a simulated environment suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and simulation (cs.SY). Finally, the use of experimental results suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) for evaluating the performance of the proposed method.
